cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper discusses multimodal models for learning semantic representations, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also mentions the use of interpretation methods based on brain-based componential semantics, which suggests a focus on explainability and interpretability in ML models, making cs.LG (Learning) another likely category. The use of multimodal models also suggests a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the mention of brain-based semantics may also suggest a connection to neural networks (cs.NE).
